        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 6:52AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 652 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Newburg, or 23 miles southwest of Bottineau, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newburg, Russell, and Kramer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
